## Why This Is Asked
Tests ability to design CGO with callbacks, handling Go/C boundaries, memory ownership, and error propagation under concurrency.

## Key Concepts
- Go-C callbacks across CGO
- Memory lifetime and freeing in mixed languages
- Error propagation and backpressure in streaming APIs
- Worker pool design for streaming data

## Code Example
```c
// streaming.h
typedef void (*chunk_cb_t)(const uint8_t* data, size_t len, void* ctx);
int streaming_transform(const uint8_t* input, size_t length, chunk_cb_t cb, void* ctx);
```

```c
// streaming.c
#include "streaming.h"
#include <stdlib.h>

int streaming_transform(const uint8_t* input, size_t length, chunk_cb_t cb, void* ctx) {
  if (!input || length == 0) return 0;
  const size_t CHUNK = 1024;
  size_t remaining = length;
  const uint8_t* p = input;
  while (remaining > 0) {
    size_t take = remaining < CHUNK ? remaining : CHUNK;
    cb(p, take, ctx);
    p += take;
    remaining -= take;
  }
  return 0;
}
```

